Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.81,0:00:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上好，欢迎收看《卡尔佩珀分钟》。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Good evening, and welcome to The Culpeper Minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.57,0:00:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,距离那本畅销自传《兜帽之下》揭露初代蒙面冒险家团队——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's been nearly a decade. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.11,0:00:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,——新生民兵的秘密，已过去近十年时光。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...since the best-selling autobiography Under the Hood...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,1975年，《卡尔佩珀分钟》首度登陆广播频道时……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...revealed secrets of the original band of masked adventurers...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.45,0:00:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,……我们曾专访《兜帽之下》的作者霍利斯·梅森……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the new Minutemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.74,0:00:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,……那位以"夜枭"之名闻名的前冒险家。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In 1975, when The Culpeper Minute was new to the airwaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.16,0:00:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,当我的原始报道在1975年播出时，《基恩法案》尚未通过。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}. . .we profiled the author of Under the Hood, Hollis Mason. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.21,0:00:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,如今，这项颇具争议的法案已将一切变装冒险家与蒙面英雄定为非法。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the former adventurer known as Nite Owl.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.09,0:00:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,鉴于当前社会对蒙面正义议题的动荡氛围……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}When my original report aired in 1 975, the Keene Act had not yet been passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.97,0:00:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,……我们认为重温当年那期节目会颇具深意……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, this controversial bill outlawed all costumed adventurers and masked heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.72,0:00:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,……以此提醒人们这场变装英雄现象的……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Given our current climate of unrest around the subject of masked justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.77,0:01:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,……起源之地。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...we thought it would be interesting to revisit that original episode...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.77,0:01:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚我们将与霍利斯·梅森畅谈他的自传《兜帽之下》。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}. . .as a reminder of where the whole phenomena. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.48,0:01:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,霍利斯·梅森的回忆录揭示了蒙面冒险家们……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...of costumed heroics began.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.16,0:01:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,……不为人知的秘密。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Tonight we're talking with Hollis Mason about his autobiography, Under the Hood.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.87,0:01:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hollis Mason's memoirs revealed some of the secrets...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hollis Mason's memoirs revealed some of the secrets...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.79,0:01:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,...of the masked adventurers.\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...of the masked adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.50,0:01:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我在霍利斯最喜欢的纽约餐厅之一——恒河餐厅与他见面。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I met with Hollis at one of his favorite New York establishments, the Gunga Diner.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.67,0:01:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,十二岁来到纽约……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Coming to New York at 1 2 years old...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.97,0:01:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,……在很多方面，这对我来说，呃，都棒极了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...it was, uh, fantastic for me in a lot of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.31,0:01:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我父亲在第七大道旁的弗农汽车修理店找到了一份工作。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And my dad got a job at Vernon's Auto Repair off 7th Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.98,0:01:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,-现在是梅森汽修，对吧？ -现在是梅森汽修。对，对。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}-Now Mason's, right? -Now Mason's. Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.56,0:01:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,同一个地方。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.82,0:01:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,卡尔佩珀：但你并没有追随父亲的脚步。你选择了另一条路。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}CULPEPER: Yet you didn't follow in your father's footsteps. You chose another path.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.36,0:01:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,梅森：嗯，是的，当我二十三岁时……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MASON: Well, yeah, when l was 23...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.20,0:01:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,……我加入了纽约市警察局。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...l joined the New York City Police Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.49,0:02:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为这很大程度上与我祖父有关……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And l think that that had a lot to do with my grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.29,0:02:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,……以及他灌输给我的价值观。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and the values that he'd instilled in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.33,0:02:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,因为在我人生的前十二年，我大部分时间都和祖父在一起。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Because for the first 1 2 years of my life, I spent a lot of time with my granddad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.29,0:02:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,他总是热衷于让我铭记……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He was always keen to impress upon me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.46,0:02:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,……乡下人在道德上比城里人更健康，这是他们的生活方式。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that country folk were morally healthier than city folk, the way they lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.18,0:02:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,当然，在某些方面你们会相互竞争，但你们也——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Of course you were competitive in certain ways, but you were also--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.81,0:02:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你们会互相帮助。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You helped each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.14,0:02:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一种深深印在我心中的道德价值观。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And it was kind of a moral value that stuck with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.06,0:02:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,当我初到这座城市时……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And when I first got to the city...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.90,0:02:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,...我目睹的一些事 真的让我感到恶心...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...there were things l saw that really filled me with disgust...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.45,0:02:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,...我很难摆脱 而且 你知道 有些真的——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that l found a hard time shaking, and, you know, some really--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.74,0:02:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,有些我至今仍无法释怀。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Some of it l still can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.34,0:02:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我祖父教给我的...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What my grandfather gave me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.55,0:03:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,...以及我在城市里所面对的——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and what I was confronted with in the city--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.47,0:03:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,当这两者之间的差距太大 我无法承受时...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}When the distance between those things got too great and I couldn't deal with it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.56,0:03:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,...我就会逃往我真正的另一个世界 通俗小说的世界。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...then l would go to my real other world, the world of pulp-fiction novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.94,0:03:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,它们描绘了一个绝对价值的世界...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They described a world of absolute values...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.65,0:03:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,...在那里 善与真从不被质疑。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...where what was good and true was never in doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.78,0:03:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,而恶——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And evil was--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.78,0:03:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯 它总会得到应有的惩罚。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, it received its appropriate punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.58,0:03:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,那么 你就是这样度过一生的吗？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Is that how you've led your life, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.87,0:03:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,-我一直努力这么做 嗯... -嗯。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}-That's what I've tried to do. Um.... -Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.63,0:03:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,是的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.09,0:03:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,霍利斯·梅森 理想主义的年轻警察...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hollis Mason, idealizing young cop...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.80,0:03:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,...试图理解祖父的乡村价值观...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...trying to make sense of granddad's country values...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.76,0:03:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,...与他所生活的大都市的残酷现实。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and the grit of the big city he finds himself living in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.80,0:03:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,很快 警队及其正义品牌对年轻的梅森来说已不够。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Soon enough, the police force and its brand ofjustice is not enough for young Mason.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.60,0:03:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,长久以来痴迷于侦探通俗小说和漫画英雄主义...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Long a fan of pulp detective fiction and comic-book heroics...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.81,0:03:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,...梅森做了别人只敢幻想的事。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Mason did what others only fantasize about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.48,0:03:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,他为自己做了伪装……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He made himself a disguise...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.15,0:03:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,……在夜晚以义警的身份出动……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and set out in the nights as a vigilante...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.07,0:04:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,……按照自己的方式伸张正义。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...doling out justice on his own terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.78,0:04:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,是什么影响了梅森行为的转变？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What influenced this shift in Mason's behavior?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.00,0:04:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,想想还挺有趣的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's funny when you think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.96,0:04:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，我听过所有的——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, I've heard all the--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.29,0:04:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的笑话、所有的谣言和所有的影射。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}All the jokes and all the rumors and all the innuendos.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.71,0:04:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,对我来说，真正重要的是……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What it really comes down to for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.68,0:04:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,……是我打扮成猫头鹰打击犯罪……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...is that l dressed up like an owl and l fought crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.31,0:04:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,……因为那很有趣。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...because it was fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.89,0:04:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,也因为那是正确的事。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And because it was the right thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.27,0:04:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,还因为我确实乐在其中。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And because l darn well enjoyed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.61,0:04:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,[梅森轻笑]\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}[MASON CHUCKLES]
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.11,0:04:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我想这一切对我来说真正开始成形是在1938年。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I suppose it really started to take shape for me in 1 938.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.20,0:04:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,在我的巡逻区域，有很多孩子在读《动作漫画》的第一期。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And on my beat there were a lot of kids reading that first issue of Action Comics.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.08,0:04:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我被深深吸引，无法自拔。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was so drawn, I couldn't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.45,0:04:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我问其中一个孩子能否借来看看。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I asked one of the kids if l could borrow it and take a look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.71,0:04:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,而《超人》的第一期……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And that first issue of Superman...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.71,0:04:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,-……哇，让我震撼不已。-嗯。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}-...wow, knocked me out. -Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.01,0:05:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧，超人对你影响最大，对很多孩子也是如此。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Okay, Superman was your biggest influence, and it was to a lot of kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.47,0:05:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,但你走得更远。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But you took it even further.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.01,0:05:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,梅森：嗯，一切都在我有一天翻开报纸时改变了……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MASON: Well, it all changed when l opened the newspaper one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.73,0:05:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,……我看到这些角色从他们四色的世界中逃离出来……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and l saw that these characters had escaped from their four-color world...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.86,0:05:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,……他们现在身处报纸头条那真实的黑白世界里。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and they were now in the factual black-and-white world of the headlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.62,0:05:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,一次企图袭击和抢劫的事件被一个身影阻止了……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}An attempted assault and robbery was thwarted by a figure...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.70,0:05:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,……据说他是从上方跳入小巷的……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...who supposedly dropped into the alleyway from above...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.00,0:05:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,……脸上蒙着东西。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...with something over his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.92,0:05:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,然后他解除了三名袭击者的武装……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And he then proceeded to disarm the three attackers...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.42,0:05:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,……并狠狠地殴打了他们，导致三人全部住院。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and beat them with such severity that all three were hospitalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.63,0:05:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,报纸开始称他为“兜帽判官”。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The newspapers started calling him Hooded Justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.89,0:05:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,而那就是第一位蒙面义警。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And that was the first masked vigilante.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.85,0:05:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,当我听到那个故事时，我立刻下定决心……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And when I heard that story I made up my mind right then...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.02,0:05:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,……我要成为第二个。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...l was gonna be the second.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.86,0:06:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在需要为赞助商休息一下，但当我们回来时……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We have to take a break for our sponsors now, but when we come back...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.28,0:06:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,……我们将继续讲述1975年关于蒙面冒险家的故事。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...more from our 1 975 story on masked adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.27,0:06:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,感谢您继续收听。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thank you for staying with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.07,0:06:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在回到对《兜帽之下》的回顾……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We return now to our retrospective look at Under the Hood...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.45,0:06:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,……以及这些男男女女对我们今天的意义。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and what these men and women mean to us today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.03,0:06:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,卡尔佩珀：你为什么想到设计猫头鹰服装？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}CULPEPER: Why did you come up with the owl costume?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.70,0:06:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,梅森：它真的是自然而然形成的……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MASON: It really came together...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.79,0:06:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,...因为局里和我共事的另一个警察。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...because of another cop that l was working with in my station house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.88,0:07:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,他总在问下班后要不要一起去喝一杯。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And he kept asking me to go out for a beer after work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.25,0:07:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,而我总在拒绝，因为，你知道，我晚上要训练...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And l kept saying no, because, you know, I wanted to train at night...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.30,0:07:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,...为我另一份事业做准备。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and get ready for my other career.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.47,0:07:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,然后他就开始叫我"夜猫子"。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And then he started calling me "night owl."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.30,0:07:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,-你知道，他是在挖苦我。-没错。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}-You know, he was being sarcastic. -Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.31,0:07:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,但我很喜欢。我想，"好吧，就叫夜猫子吧。"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And l loved it. I thought, "Well, that's it, Nite Owl."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.94,0:07:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,-所以名字就是这么来的？-就是这么来的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}-So that's where the name came from? -That's where it came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.77,0:07:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,有了名字后，我就开始构思服装。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So once l had the name, then I could start thinking about the costume.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.24,0:07:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,该不该有披风？该不该戴面具？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Should it have a cape or no cape? Should you have a mask or no mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.03,0:07:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,最终，我把它精简到了最基本的要素。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Eventually, l just boiled it down to the basics.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.91,0:07:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要一套能自由活动的服装。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I needed a costume where l was free to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.08,0:07:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要保护身体。我需要保护头部。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I needed to protect my body. I needed to protect my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.91,0:07:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我还需要隐藏身份。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And l needed to protect my identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.67,0:07:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我做了这件覆盖着皮革和锁子甲的上衣...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So l did this with a tunic that was covered in leather and mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.01,0:07:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,...一种钢制网眼。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...a kind of steel mesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.63,0:07:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我还有个头罩——同样是皮革和钢网制成的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And l had a hood with-- It was leather and steel mesh again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.76,0:07:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,然后是短裤。也覆盖着同样的锁子甲。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And then briefs. They were covered in the same mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.73,0:07:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我把头发遮起来，只需要一个小面具。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So l've got my hair covered and all l need is a little mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.35,0:08:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,于是我用这个做了面具，就是这个面具。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So l did it with this. This is the mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.98,0:08:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我用酒精胶粘上了这个面具……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I attached this mask with a spirit gum...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.69,0:08:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,……就是演员用来贴胡子和假须的那种。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...which is what actors use to put on mustaches and beards.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.74,0:08:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,卡尔佩珀：结果发现，当时有好几个蒙面的冒险者。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}CULPEPER: lt turned out, there were several masked adventurers at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.91,0:08:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,梅森：是的，在我首次亮相大约一个月后……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MASON: Yeah, about a month after I made my debut...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.66,0:08:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,……头条新闻都是关于一个叫剪影的年轻女子。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the headlines were all about a young woman called the Silhouette.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.50,0:08:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,她揭露了一个经营儿童色情制品的奸诈出版商。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She had exposed a crooked publisher who was dealing in child pornography.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.71,0:08:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,她还狠狠地揍了他一顿。他和他的两个摄影师，对吧？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And she gave him such a brutal beating. Him and his two cameramen, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.39,0:08:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯，那真是个轰动一时的故事。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, that was quite a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.22,0:08:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,从那以后，事情发展得相当快。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}From there it grew pretty quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.65,0:08:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,有传闻说有个穿得像飞蛾的男人……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There were stories of a man dressed like a moth...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.28,0:08:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,……能在空中滑翔。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...who could glide through the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.91,0:08:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,后来又有个故事，讲的是一个穿黄色连体工装服的男人……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And then there was a story of a man in a yellow boiler suit...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.41,0:09:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,……他特别残忍和恶毒。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...who was particularly brutal and vicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.50,0:09:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,在兜帽判官戏剧性登场后的12个月里……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In 12 months of Hooded Justice's dramatic entrance...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.80,0:09:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,……至少出现了，哦，其他七个穿戏服的义务警员。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...there were at least, oh, seven other costumed vigilantes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.68,0:09:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,还有莎莉·朱庇特，她取了丝魂这个名字。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There was Sally Jupiter, who took the name of Silk Spectre.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.14,0:09:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,有美钞比尔，有飞蛾人……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There was Dollar Bill, there was Mothman...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.48,0:09:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,……有剪影侠，有笑匠。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...there was the Silhouette, there was Comedian.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.94,0:09:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,当然，还有我。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And, of course, there was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.81,0:09:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,梅森告诉我的事情，大多已写在他的书里。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Little that Mason told me was not already in his book.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.90,0:09:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,于是我转向他世界里的其他人物，以了解更多。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So l turned to some of the other figures from his world to find out more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.45,0:09:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,她利用自己的性感来打击犯罪……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She used her sexuality to fight crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.16,0:09:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,……又凭借打击犯罪的经历在银幕上谋求事业。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and her crime fighting to pursue a career on the silver screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.75,0:09:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,如今她的女儿延续着她的形象……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now her daughter lives on in her image...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.58,0:09:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,……而生活似乎已将莎莉·朱庇特抛在身后。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and life seemingly has passed Sally Jupiter by.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.13,0:09:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,1975年，我们在她家中进行了以下对话。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We joined her at her home for the following exchange back in 1 975.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.55,0:09:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,卡尔佩珀：为何取名丝魂？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}CULPEPER: Why the name Silk Spectre?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.01,0:09:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,朱庇特：说来有趣。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JUPITER: You know, it's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.39,0:10:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,很多人猜测过这个名字的由来。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Many people have hypothesized about reasons why that might have come up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.48,0:10:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,而事实上，我只是想找个神秘的名字……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And in truth, I wanted to find something mysterious...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.19,0:10:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,……听起来顺耳的那种，明白吗？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...something that had a good ring to it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.36,0:10:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得她应该是那种能从你指缝中溜走的人物。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And l felt that she should be somebody who could slip out of your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.03,0:10:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,要知道，当时丝袜非常昂贵。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Silk stockings, you know, were very expensive at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.36,0:10:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我想，这名字确实朗朗上口——我只能这么解释了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And it just had a good ring to it, l guess, is all I can really say.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.24,0:10:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你成为蒙面冒险家的动机是什么？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What were your motivations in becoming a masked adventurer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.50,0:10:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我看到了兜帽判官……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I saw Hooded Justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.21,0:10:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,……我觉得做点不同寻常的事——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and l think the idea of doing something that was out of the normal--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.88,0:10:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我从未觉得自己真正融入过。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I never felt like l really fit in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.76,0:10:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,而成为丝鬼确实让我感觉更像找到了归属。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And l think that becoming Silk Spectre really made me feel actually more at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.22,0:10:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,如今，丝鬼在海报和漫画中的形象都相当大胆。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, Silk Spectre is presented in fairly racy imagery in posters and in comics.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.93,0:10:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你如何处理这些我称之为视觉贬低的图片？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}How do you deal with these, what I call, visually degrading pictures?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.81,0:10:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,哦，我对那种事从来没什么意见。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, l never had a problem with that sort of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.90,0:10:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说，你知道，他们总把我称作性感符号。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I mean, you know, they always referred to me as a sex symbol.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.70,0:10:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我得说，我宁愿成为那样的符号……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And l have to say, I'd rather be a symbol of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.20,0:11:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,……也不愿成为他们那些其他符号的象征。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...than a symbol for other things they've got symbols of.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.28,0:11:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你明白我的意思吗？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know what l mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.95,0:11:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,吉米·范图奇，一个著名的黑帮分子，我相信你听说过他。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jimmy Fantucci, a famous mobster, I'm sure you've heard of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.54,0:11:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他实际上向警方自首了，因为他无法对我开枪。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He actually turned himself into the cops because he couldn't shoot me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.34,0:11:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，正如我所说，我从不回避自己的外貌。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, as l said, l never shied away from the way that I looked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.71,0:11:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,而且，事实上，在这种情况下，我似乎可以利用它。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And, in fact, it seemed in this case, I could use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.97,0:11:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,蒙面冒险家或随便你们怎么称呼他们本质上都是商业行为。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Masked adventurers or whatever what you wanna call them is all about commerce.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.01,0:11:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你们必须记住这个国家是建立在娱乐业之上的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You have to remember that this country was founded on entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.60,0:11:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,当我管理丝鬼萨莉时……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And when I managed Sally, the Silk Spectre...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.60,0:11:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,……我们利用她作为蒙面英雄的身份达成了各种利润丰厚的交易。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...we used her status as a costumed hero to make lucrative deals of every kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.44,0:11:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,电影合约、海报形象授权、漫画书，无所不包。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Movie deals, image licensing for pinups, comic books, everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.11,0:11:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,这种商业策略几乎立刻就被各大企业采纳了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It was a business strategy that corporations picked up on almost immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.54,0:11:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,美元比尔原本是堪萨斯州的大学体育明星……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dollar Bill was originally a star college athlete from Kansas...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.41,0:11:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,……被一家大型百货公司聘用……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...hired by a major department store...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.37,0:11:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,……因为他们意识到拥有自己的超级英雄……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...when they realized that having their own superhero...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.13,0:11:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,……是个颇具前景的宣传策略。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...was an interesting publicity prospect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.38,0:11:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,不过我还是认为萨莉和我开创了这个概念。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Still, l like to think that Sally and I pioneered the concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.97,0:12:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,当你想在世界上留下印记时，你需要帮助。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}When you're trying to make a mark in the world, you need help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.39,0:12:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你需要一个能起到凝聚作用的人……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You need someone who can be sort of the cohesive factor...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.35,0:12:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,……将这种意识传递给公众，而他确实做到了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...in bringing the awareness to the public, and he definitely did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.31,0:12:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,而且我认为，实际上这可能牺牲了许多人的计划。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And l think, in fact, probably at the expense of many people's agendas, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.19,0:12:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我不认为你能做出价值判断……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't think you can make value judgments...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.48,0:12:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,……关于蒙面英雄对社会是好是坏。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...on whether or not costumed heroes are good or bad for society.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.11,0:12:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,这就像问电视是好是坏一样。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's like asking if television is good or bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.12,0:12:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,答案是两者皆有。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The answer is that it's both.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.12,0:12:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,真正的问题始于我们聚在一起之后……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It was only really when we got together...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.66,0:12:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,……问题才真正开始。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that the problems started.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.75,0:12:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,是的，就是民兵组织。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The Minutemen, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.09,0:12:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,多棒的主意啊。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What a great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.59,0:12:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我真希望这功劳能归我，但凭良心说我不能。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I wish I can take credit for it, but I can't in good conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.18,0:12:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,事情是这样的，有一天我收到了大都会队长写给莎莉的信。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The way it happened was one day l got a letter for Sally from Captain Metropolis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.43,0:12:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他说他想聚在一起讨论这个想法……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He said he wanted to get together to discuss the idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.93,0:12:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,……组建一个蒙面冒险家团体。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...of forming a group of masked adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.52,0:12:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,起初，我以为他是想用这个主意作为把她弄上床的手段。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}At first, I thought he was using the idea as a means to get her into bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.48,0:12:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我做了一些调查……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then l did a little research...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.53,0:13:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,……我了解到我的担忧……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and l learned that my concerns...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.91,0:13:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,……是的，是没有根据的……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...were, yeah, unfounded...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.78,0:13:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,……如果你明白我的意思的话。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...if you get my meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.12,0:13:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,劳伦斯创建了民兵组织。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Lawrence made the Minutemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.83,0:13:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,如果不是因为他和他的宣传天赋——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If it wasn't for him and his knack for publicity--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.00,0:13:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我想，作为你这一行的人，你大概能理解……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I mean l think as someone in your profession, you could probably understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.13,0:13:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,……如果我们做了这次采访却没人看到，那么，噗，一切就都不重要了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that if we did this interview and no one saw it, then, poof, it doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.88,0:13:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,谢克奈德：我意识到如果没有偶尔的噱头……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}SHEXNAYDER: I realized that without the occasional gimmick...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.80,0:13:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,……来重振日渐衰落的公众兴趣……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to revitalize flagging public interest...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.31,0:13:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,……这些穿着奇装异服的英雄热潮……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the fad of costumed heroes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.14,0:13:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,……最终会逐渐消退，即使是那些打扮得像莎莉的人也不例外。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...would eventually fade, even the ones dressed like Sally.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.06,0:13:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,经过一番考虑，我建议他们在《公报》上刊登一则大幅广告……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}After some consideration l suggested they take a large ad out in the Gazette...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.90,0:13:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,……邀请更多神秘人物挺身而出。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...asking for more mystery men to come forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.90,0:13:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是"民兵"组织的由来。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And that's how the Minutemen came to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.03,0:13:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,卡尔佩珀：那么，当你第一次见到"笑匠"时……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}CULPEPER: Now, when you first met The Comedian...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.16,0:13:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,……"夜枭"、"剪影"和其他人……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Nite Owl, Silhouette and the others...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.41,0:13:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,……你当时有什么想法？你感到害怕吗？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...what were your thoughts? Were you intimidated?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.96,0:13:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,是否有一种如释重负的感觉？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Was there a sense of relief?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.75,0:13:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,哦，我必须说，那是一个令人难以置信的振奋人心的时期。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, it was an incredibly exhilarating time, I have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:14:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我想我们都觉得自己是家庭的一部分……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think we all felt like we were part of a family...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.09,0:14:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,……我们找到了某种归属地……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that we had found sort of a place...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.05,0:14:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,……在那里我们可以感觉自己确实是有价值的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...where we could feel like we actually were of value.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.85,0:14:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人都为"民兵"带来了不同的东西。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Everyone brought something different to the Minutemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.52,0:14:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,但不知何故，当我们在一起时，有一种团结的感觉……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But somehow when we were together there was a bonding feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.06,0:14:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,……我们都相信我们所做的事情。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that we all believed in what we were doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.60,0:14:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,现在，我之所以说"如释重负"，是因为在那个年代，许多人……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, the reason I say "relief" is because many of the people back in those days...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.86,0:14:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,...认为你们都是相当古怪、不正常的人...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...thought that you were all rather bizarre, abnormal individuals...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.82,0:14:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,...穿着儿童服装到处跑。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...running around in children's costumes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.91,0:14:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,朱庇特：我们只是普通人。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JUPITER: We were just people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.41,0:14:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,而且每个人的政治立场确实完全不同。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And everyone did have absolutely different politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.50,0:14:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我们中有些人是为了名声。有些人是为了权力。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Some of us were in it for fame. Some for power.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.37,0:14:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,有些人可能是为了躲避这个世界。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Some to possibly hide from the rest of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.50,0:14:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,但归根结底，我们的政治立场并没有太多妨碍...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But in the end of the day, our politics really didn't get in the way too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.67,0:14:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,...我们想要在那里做的事情，这是好事。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...of what we wanted to be there to do, which was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.55,0:14:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在各自的社区做了太多好事，不能被一笔勾销。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We did too much good in our respective communities just to be written off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.60,0:14:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都试图通过个人的努力...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We were all attempting through our personal efforts...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.64,0:14:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,...让我们的国家成为一个更好、更安全的居住地。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to make our country a better and a safer place to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.98,0:15:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,显然，霍利斯·梅森是一个对自己的人生...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Clearly, Hollis Mason is a man who makes no apologies...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.32,0:15:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,...或所做的决定毫不后悔的人。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...for the life he's lived or the decisions he's made.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.07,0:15:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,但他个人的道德准则是否足以成为...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But is his own personal moral code enough justification...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.66,0:15:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,...戴上面具、执行私刑正义的理由？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...for donning a mask and dispensing vigilante justice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.04,0:15:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我出去四处询问，以更好地了解...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I went out and asked around to get a better sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.21,0:15:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,...你们，人民，对蒙面英雄的看法。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...of how you, the people, felt about masked heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.13,0:15:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,男子1：我不知道。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 1 : I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.97,0:15:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我这儿有很多顾客是警察。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I get a lot of customers that are cops.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.01,0:15:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,他们常来我这儿买包烟...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Guys that come by and pay for a pack of smokes from me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.60,0:15:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,...然后告诉我这些蒙面义警...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and they tell me that these masked adventurers...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.35,0:15:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,...让他们的工作变得更难了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...they're making the job more difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.48,0:15:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,男子2：我怎么看他们？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 2: What do I think of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.32,0:15:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,他们几乎毁了我的生意，我可以这么说。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They've just about destroyed my business, I can tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.74,0:15:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,他们把我的顾客弄成残废。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They maim my customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.70,0:15:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,他们喜欢折断手指。他们觉得这很有趣。是的。他们很危险。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They like to break fingers. They think it's funny. Yeah. They're dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.58,0:15:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,但另一方面，如果我们没有...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But then on the other hand, what if we hadn't had...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.41,0:15:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,...那个曼哈顿博士站在我们这边，会怎样呢？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that Dr. Manhattan guy on our side, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.42,0:16:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说，我知道以我们现在所知来看，这难以想象...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I mean, l know it's inconceivable to us, now knowing what we know...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.21,0:16:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,...但谁能说没有他们...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but who's to say that things wouldn't have gone the same in Vietnam...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.88,0:16:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,...越南的情况就不会一样呢？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...without them?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.38,0:16:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,输掉那场战争。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Losing that war.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.26,0:16:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,那会毁掉我们的国家。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That would've destroyed our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.01,0:16:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,更多关于蒙面义警及其引发的争议...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}More on costumed adventurers and the controversy surrounding them...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.56,0:16:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,...将在赞助商信息后继续播报。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...after this word from our sponsors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.65,0:16:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,播报员：精工宣布推出世界首款数字石英液晶计时码表。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ANNOUNCER: Seiko announces the world's first digital quartz, liquid crystal chronograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.11,0:16:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,它能显示时间、日期...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}lt gives the time, the date...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.90,0:16:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,...并且按下一个按钮，就能变成秒表...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and with a push of a button, turns into a stopwatch...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.70,0:16:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,...记录着圈速和冠亚军成绩，精确到十分之一秒。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that records lap times and one-two finishes in tenths of seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.95,0:16:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,按下按钮，储存在电子记忆中的时间便会再次显现。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The time of day, kept in electronic memory, reappears when you push the button again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.79,0:16:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,精工液晶计时码表。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The Seiko liquid crystal chronograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.08,0:16:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这只是精工卓越数字石英腕表中的一款。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Only one of Seiko's superb digital quartz watches.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.80,0:16:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎回来，感谢您的收看。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Welcome back, and thank you for watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.43,0:16:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,在当前环境下，蒙面冒险者——守望者们的现实意义...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In our current climate, the relevance of masked adventurers, the Watchmen...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.35,0:17:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,...比以往任何时候都更受质疑。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...is more in question than ever before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.60,0:17:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在继续回顾一档节目...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We continue now with our look back at a show...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.06,0:17:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,...其中我们讨论了《兜帽之下》...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...in which we discussed Under the Hood...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.27,0:17:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...一本关于初代蒙面英雄夜枭（原名霍利斯·梅森）的回忆录。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...a memoir of original masked hero The Nite Owl, née Hollis Mason.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.11,0:17:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,这本书引出了许多我们至今仍在探讨的问题...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A book which precipitated many of the questions we have today...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.49,0:17:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,...关于这些游离于既定法律之外的男男女女。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...about these men and women who act apart from our prescribed laws ofjustice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.13,0:17:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,当然，有许多身着戏服的英雄值得深入研究。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Certainly there are many costumed heroes who would make for fascinating study.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.93,0:17:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾与精神病学家威廉·朗交谈...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I spoke with psychiatrist William Long...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.72,0:17:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,...以获取一些专业见解。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to gain some professional insight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.93,0:17:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,您知道，这是个有趣的问题。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, it's an interesting question.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.56,0:17:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,大多数时候，我在监狱里与罪犯打交道。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mostly, in the prison, I work with criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.82,0:17:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我的看法可能略有偏差。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So my perception is slightly skewed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.90,0:17:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为肯定有蒙面英雄……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think certainly there are masked heroes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.41,0:17:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,……和超人类，比如曼哈顿博士……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and superhumans, like Dr. Manhattan...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.99,0:18:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,……他们只想做好事。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that just want to do good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.16,0:18:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为还有一些人不过是罪犯……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think there are others that are nothing more than criminals...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.13,0:18:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,……他们以此为手段……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...who used this as a means...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.84,0:18:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,……来为自己的暴力倾向辩护。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to justify their violent tendencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.34,0:18:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,真正构成实际威胁的蒙面英雄……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The only masked heroes that pose an actual threat...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.81,0:18:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,……是那些相对少数的边缘反社会者……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...are the relatively few borderline sociopaths...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.44,0:18:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,……他们真心相信自己是在行善。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that actually believe that they are doing good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.02,0:18:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,在那面具之下……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Beneath that mask...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.36,0:18:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,……他们就像你我一样……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...they're just like you and me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.15,0:18:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,……有希望和欲望，有恐惧……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...with hopes and desires, fears...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.58,0:18:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,……有爱。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...love.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.87,0:18:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望有一天……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I hope that one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.50,0:18:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,……我能为这些蒙面英雄中的一位做心理分析。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...l can psychoanalyze one of these masked heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.05,0:18:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,那会很有意思。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That would be something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.71,0:18:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,如今看来那似乎是一个逝去的时代。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It seems a bygone era to us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.97,0:18:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,喧嚣的四十年代，令人陶醉的日子。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The heady days of the roaring '40s.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.47,0:19:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,人们渴望分心，渴求戏剧性的刺激。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}People were eager for distraction, hungry for a fix of drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.89,0:19:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,还有什么比一群自封的超级英雄……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What better than a group of self-designed superheroes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.23,0:19:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,……上演一场夸张的街头犯罪打击戏剧更好的呢？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to act out an exaggerated street theater of crime fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.73,0:19:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,在一个充斥着超级反派的世界里……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And in a world populated by supervillains...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.07,0:19:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,……何乐而不为呢？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.86,0:19:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,有臭名昭著的神秘法师莫洛克……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There was the notorious Moloch the Mystic...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.90,0:19:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,……利用魔术表演的杂耍新奇感来掩饰他单枪匹马的恐怖浪潮。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...using the sideshow novelty of the magic show to front his one-man wave of terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.41,0:19:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,当然，后来出现了像大人物这样的现代超级反派……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Later, of course, came modern supervillains like Big Figure...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.08,0:19:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,……这位身材矮小的犯罪大师如今正在市监狱服无期徒刑。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the diminutive master criminal now serving a life sentence in the city jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.26,0:19:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你以为我是威胁。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You think I'm the menace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.93,0:19:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我可不是那个戴面具的人。我没什么好隐瞒的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm not the one wearing a mask. I got nothing to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.81,0:19:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,那是什么样的人？戴面具？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What kind of person is that? Wear a mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.90,0:19:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我是个受人尊敬的商人。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm a respectable businessman.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.15,0:19:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,卡尔佩珀：找到神秘法师莫洛克可不容易。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}CULPEPER: It wasn't easy finding Moloch the Mystic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.78,0:19:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,但话说回来，嗯，也没那么难。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But then again, well, it wasn't too difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.41,0:20:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你看，莫洛克，就像我们战后历史上许多臭名昭著的人物一样……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You see, Moloch, like so many infamous figures of our postwar past...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.62,0:20:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,……只是过上了平民生活。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...had simply gone into civilian life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.00,0:20:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,莫洛克：那时我还年轻。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MOLOCH: I was a younger man then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.58,0:20:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我很叛逆。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was rebellious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.00,0:20:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,就像你看到的这些帮派，结顶帮。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Like these gangs you see around, the Knot Tops.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.96,0:20:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,当你生活在一个有超人类权威人物的世界里……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}When you live in a world with superhuman authority figures...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.93,0:20:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,……而你想反抗，你就必须进行更大规模的抗争。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and you wanna rebel, you have to rebel on a larger scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.84,0:20:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你得把事情升级，明白吗。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You have to escalate things, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.43,0:20:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,所以……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.60,0:20:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,……如果你在一个有超级英雄的世界里长大，而你想反抗……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...if you grow up in a world with superheroes and you wanna rebel...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.35,0:20:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,……你就必须成为超级反派。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you have to become a supervillain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.65,0:20:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,所以，是的，我认为没有超级英雄的社会会更好……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So, yeah, l think society is better off without the superheroes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.20,0:20:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,……因为那也意味着不再需要任何超级反派。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...because that means there's no need for any supervillains either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.96,0:20:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,梅森：谢谢。谢谢。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MASON: Thank you. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.29,0:20:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，它并没有持续，哦，十年。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, it didn't last, oh, 1 0 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.22,0:21:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,当五十年代到来时，人们对蒙面冒险家的整体看法……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}When the '50s came, the whole perception of costumed adventurers...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.10,0:21:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,……你知道，改变了，明白吗？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you know, changed, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.35,0:21:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,那是一种潮流，是的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It was a fad, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.68,0:21:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,而潮流正在消退，我们也随之消逝。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And the fad was dying out and we were dying with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.52,0:21:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,[轻笑]\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}[CHUCKLES]
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.02,0:21:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,莎莉……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sally...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.77,0:21:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,……嗯，她怀孕了，然后离开了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...well, she got pregnant and she left.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.53,0:21:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我们剩下的人，被迫在……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The rest of us, we were forced to testify...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.95,0:21:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,……众议院非美活动调查委员会前作证。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...before the House Un-American Activities Committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.53,0:21:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,那是一场政治迫害。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It was a witch hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.20,0:21:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都被迫向其中一位代表……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We were all forced to reveal our identities...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.75,0:21:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,……透露了我们的真实身份。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to one of its representatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.33,0:21:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我是来自民兵组织的首都队长。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I am Captain Metropolis from the Minutemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.38,0:21:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,梅森：现在，幸运的是，由于首都队长……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MASON: Now, luckily, with Captain Metropolis...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.46,0:21:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,……拥有如此出色的军事记录……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...having such an outstanding military record...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.76,0:21:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,……再加上我自己在警察部门的服务……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and with my own service in the police force...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.05,0:21:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,……我们俩或多或少都立刻摆脱了嫌疑。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...we both were more or less cleared of suspicion right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.06,0:21:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,飞蛾侠遇到了更多困难，主要是因为他那些左翼朋友……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mothman met with more difficulty, mostly because of the left-wing friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.64,0:21:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,那是他在学生时代培养起来的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that he'd cultivated during his student days.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.23,0:21:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,如今他终于洗清了冤屈……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, he's eventually cleared...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.07,0:22:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,但调查过程如此漫长且残酷……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but the investigations, they were so lengthy and so ruthless...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.74,0:22:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,以至于我认为他所承受的压力……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that l think that the pressure he was under...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.57,0:22:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,加剧了他的酗酒问题……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...it exacerbated his drinking problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.95,0:22:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,并最终导致了他的精神崩溃。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and it caused his eventual mental breakdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.21,0:22:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,兜帽判官……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hooded Justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.59,0:22:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,拒绝作证……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...refused to testify...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.09,0:22:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,理由是他不准备向任何人透露自己的真实身份。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...on the grounds that he was not prepared to reveal his true identity to anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.43,0:22:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,而当他们逼迫他时……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And when they pressed him...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.18,0:22:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,他便消失了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...he disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.48,0:22:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,为此我十分敬重他。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And l really respect him for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.44,0:22:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,正是因为他，我才成为了夜枭……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He was the reason I became the Nite Owl...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.48,0:22:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,而时至今日，我仍不知面具后的他究竟是谁。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and l don't know to this day who he was behind that mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.45,0:22:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这难道不令人感慨吗？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Isn't that something?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.70,0:22:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[轻笑]\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}[CHUCKLES]
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.32,0:22:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我了解到你离开民兵组织是因为怀孕了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I understand that you wanted to leave the Minutemen because you got pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.12,0:22:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,是这个原因吗？是否还有其他理由……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Is that the reason? Was there any other reasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.29,0:22:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,让你从民兵组织退役？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that you retired from the Minutemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.50,0:22:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,朱庇特：你知道，有时候只是到了该向前看的时候。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JUPITER: You know, sometimes it's just time to move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.84,0:23:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我想如果没有怀孕，我可能会待得更久一些。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think I would've stayed longer, had l not gotten pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.42,0:23:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但事实是——你知道，生活总会给你一些小小的提示，告诉你何时该退出。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But it was-- You know, life gives you those little signs of when to take the door out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.97,0:23:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,而那次似乎就是那个时机。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And that seemed to be the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.05,0:23:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,在他的传记中，霍利斯声称你曾遭到喜剧演员的性侵。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In his biography, Hollis alleged that you were sexually assaulted by The Comedian.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.89,0:23:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,但你对此从未发表过任何言论。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yet you've never said anything about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.65,0:23:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.48,0:23:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,那么，我为什么要打破一辈子的习惯呢，对吧？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, why should l break a lifetime's habit now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.44,0:23:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[轻笑]\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}[CHUCKLES]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.78,0:23:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,作为记者，我理解你的提问，但，是的，这件事——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I can't blame you for asking as a reporter, but, yes, it's--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.20,0:23:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,无可奉告。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.41,0:23:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,莎莉·朱庇特和喜剧演员之间的事件……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}How much did the incident between Sally Jupiter and The Comedian...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.37,0:23:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,……对你决定摘下面具有多大影响？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...affect your decision to hang up the mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.96,0:23:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯，那确实有很大关系，是的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, that had lot to do with it, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.67,0:23:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我想一旦你意识到你的某些队友……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think once you realize that some of your teammates...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.72,0:23:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,……和你追捕的罪犯一样堕落……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...are just as depraved...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.51,0:23:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,……一样扭曲……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and twisted as the criminals you're going after....
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.31,0:23:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,是的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.52,0:24:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我退出的主要原因。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That had a lot to do with why I quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.36,0:24:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,那个传闻并非事实。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There's no truth to that rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.57,0:24:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,如果真发生了那样的事……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If something like that had happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.53,0:24:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,……难道你不认为我会建议莎莉提起刑事诉讼吗？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...don't you think I would have advised Sally to have pressed criminal charges?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.33,0:24:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,她是我最好的客户。是我最大的收入来源。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She was my best client. My biggest earner.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.45,0:24:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我绝不会让那样的事逍遥法外。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I would never allow something like that to go unpunished.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.71,0:24:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,这不过是哗众取宠罢了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's nothing more than sensationalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.21,0:24:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,自我炒作而已。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Self-promotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.92,0:24:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,霍利斯·梅森想多卖几本书。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hollis Mason wants to sell more books.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.67,0:24:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,卡尔佩珀：笑匠拒绝发表评论。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}CULPEPER: The Comedian declined to comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.26,0:24:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,把那玩意儿从我面前拿开，否则我就把雪茄按在你眼睛里。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Get that thing out of my face before l put my cigar out in your eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.43,0:24:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,《面罩之下》是本精彩绝伦的书。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Under the Hood is a fantastic book.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.06,0:24:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,要知道，他也是我的顾客之一。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, he's one of my customers, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.35,0:24:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我经常能见到他。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I see him all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.69,0:24:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,关于超级英雄这事儿很有意思，要知道，那条界限非常微妙。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's funny about this superhero thing, you know, it's a very fine line.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.48,0:24:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,当你遇到像夜枭这样的人……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And when you got somebody like the Nite Owl...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.61,0:24:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他是典型的超级英雄，因为在外人看来这家伙……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...who is your quintessential superhero, because outside you get this guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.99,0:24:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,穿着戏服整天打打杀杀轰轰烈烈……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...who dresses up and does all the kaboom-kabang stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.70,0:24:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,但内里他其实是个警察。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but inside he's a cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.62,0:25:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,所以他是个明辨是非的人。明白我的意思吗？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So he's a guy who knows what's true blue. You know what l mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.00,0:25:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,他不搞那些花里胡哨的名堂。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He's not into these kind of artsy-fartsy things.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.38,0:25:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,他是个了不起的人。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He's a great man.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.67,0:25:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,所以……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.26,0:25:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我也说不清。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...l don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.92,0:25:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,很难判断这些蒙面英雄到底是好是坏……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hard to say whether these masked-hero types are a good or a bad thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.97,0:25:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,要知道，归根结底是这样。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you know, in the final analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.39,0:25:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,值得注意的是早在1975年……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's interesting to note that back in 1 975...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.73,0:25:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,人们对这类存在仍存在巨大分歧……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...people were still very much divided as to whether or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.81,0:25:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,所谓的蒙面义警对社会究竟有益还是有害。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the so-called costumed adventurers were a benefit or a detriment to society.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.61,0:25:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,鉴于本次访谈播出后发生的事件……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Given the events after this interview aired...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.95,0:25:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,……或许霍利斯·梅森的退休来得正是时候。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...perhaps Hollis Mason's retirement came at the perfect time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.49,0:25:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,广告之后我们将继续聆听霍利斯·梅森的讲述。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We'll hear more from Hollis Mason after this commercial break.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.62,0:25:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,播音员：为何如此多人选择洁厕灵……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ANNOUNCER: Why do so many choose Sani-Flush...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.62,0:25:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,……而非其他主流马桶清洁剂？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...instead of the other leading bathroom-bowl cleaner?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.29,0:25:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,洁厕灵拥有超凡效力。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sani-Flush has extra power.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.00,0:25:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,清洁马桶内壁，彻底洗净弯道。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Cleans inside the bowl and cleans right round the bend.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.68,0:25:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,延时镜头显示，洁厕灵凭借其超凡效力……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Time-lapse shows Sani-Flush, with its extra power...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.47,0:25:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,……能清除锈渍与沉积物……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...cleans away rust stains and deposits...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.51,0:25:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,……深入马桶内壁，彻底洗净弯道。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...inside the bowl and right round the bend.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.10,0:26:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,洁厕灵，拥有灭杀数百万细菌的强大功效。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sani-Flush, with the power to kill germs by the millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.14,0:26:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,洁厕灵。清洁马桶内壁，彻底洗净弯道。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sani-Flush. Cleans inside the bowl and cleans right round the bend.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.23,0:26:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,选择洁厕灵，粉剂或液体均可。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Get Sani-Flush, powder or liquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.99,0:26:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,现在继续我对霍利斯·梅森的访谈。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Continuing now with my interview of Hollis Mason.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.03,0:26:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们正在讨论蒙面义警的话题。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We're talking about costumed adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.41,0:26:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,他被称为世界第八大奇迹。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He's been called the Eighth Wonder of the World.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.33,0:26:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的国家瑰宝。我们最伟大的希望。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Our national treasure. Our greatest hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.21,0:26:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,但曼哈顿博士也被视为自然界的异类。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But Dr. Manhattan is also viewed as a freak of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.54,0:26:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,他的力量如此强大，不仅令敌人恐惧，也让我们自己心生畏惧。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}His power is so great as to illicit fear not only in our enemies but in ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.21,0:26:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,在他成为今日这般散发蓝光的超能存在之前……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Before he was the radiating blue superbeing he is today...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.55,0:26:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,……他曾是乔恩·奥斯特曼，物理学家，钟表匠之子。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...he was Jon Osterman, physicist, son of a watchmaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.47,0:26:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,一个拥有友情、爱情和普通家庭观念的人。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A man with friendships, loves, common family values.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.35,0:26:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,他的一位朋友，实际上也是同事……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}One of his friends and, in fact, colleagues...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.85,0:26:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,……至今仍与曼哈顿博士共事……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...who continues to work with Dr. Manhattan today...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.65,0:26:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,……本身就是一位备受尊敬的物理学家……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...is an esteemed physicist in his own right...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.40,0:26:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,……沃利·韦弗。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Wally Weaver.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.69,0:26:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我们前往韦弗的实验室，进行了如下对话。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We went to Weaver's lab and had the following conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.53,0:26:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯，我认为……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, l think...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.70,0:27:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,……各类英雄都是好事。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...heroes of all kinds are a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.08,0:27:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我指的是我们武装部队中勇敢的男女军人。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And l'm talking about the brave men and women of our Armed Forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.71,0:27:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我指的是警察和消防员。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm talking about the policemen and the firefighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.50,0:27:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我指的是科学家和医生。还有，呃……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm talking about the scientists and the doctors. And, uh....
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.22,0:27:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,是的，我也会把蒙面英雄……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, l'd include masked heroes...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.22,0:27:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,……归入那类对社会有益的人群中。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...in that group that's a benefit to society too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.89,0:27:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,但乔恩——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jon is--
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.60,0:27:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉，曼哈顿博士……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm sorry. Dr. Manhattan...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.56,0:27:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,……完全是另一回事。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...is something else entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.61,0:27:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我正在写一本书，讲述他如何永远改变了地缘政治格局……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm writing a book about how he's changed the geopolitical landscape forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.15,0:27:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,……从根本上重塑了……的概念。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...essentially making the very idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.08,0:27:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,...使得战争过时了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...of war obsolete.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.70,0:27:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,梅森：你知道，第一反应是完全难以置信。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MASON: You know, the first thing was absolute disbelief.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.46,0:27:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,当然，正如你所知，也有狂喜。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, of course, as you know, there was elation too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.25,0:27:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我的意思是，就像圣诞老人活生生地、生机勃勃地存在。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I mean, it was like Santa Claus was alive and thriving.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.93,0:27:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,但恐惧……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But the fear....
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.22,0:28:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,那是一种可怕的恐惧……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It was a terrible fear...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.77,0:28:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,……以及一种直击你核心的不确定性。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and an uncertainty that went right to your core.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.89,0:28:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我当然能理解一辆旧车的感觉……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I certainly understood how an old car feels...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.44,0:28:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,……当它看到一辆新车，一个新车型驶出来时。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...when it sees a new car, a new model come rolling out.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.61,0:28:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,[轻笑]\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}[CHUCKLES]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.74,0:28:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,但这不止如此。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But it was more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.53,0:28:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，我想我可以用三个字来概括那种感觉，真的。那就是：\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, I think I can boil the feeling down to three words, really. lt's:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.12,0:28:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我们被取代了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We've been replaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.45,0:28:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我指的不只是那些戴面具的冒险家。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And l don't just mean the masked adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.87,0:28:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我指的是，人类。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I mean, humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.96,0:28:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我们被取代了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We've been replaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.13,0:28:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,霍利斯总是有戏剧性的天赋。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hollis always did have a flair for the dramatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.60,0:28:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,毫无疑问，这对我们所有人来说都是一个绝对的震惊。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There is no doubt that it was an absolute shock to all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.81,0:28:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,像曼哈顿博士这样的存在能够存在的事实。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The fact that anything could exist like Dr. Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.81,0:28:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我的意思是，这对我们来说是超出概念范畴的东西。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I mean, this was something out of the realm of concept for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.27,0:28:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们永远需要人性……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But we will always have a need for humanity...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.32,0:29:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,……无论我们在技术上如何扩展和成长，这是——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and as much as we expand and grow technologically, it's--
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.99,0:29:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我们仍然需要人类的接触，你知道吗？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We still need human contact, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.74,0:29:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,人们总是误解我关于乔恩的言论。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}People have always misinterpreted what I said about Jon.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.46,0:29:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我并非将他比作神明。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I wasn't comparing him to God. I wasn't saying he was a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.09,0:29:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,也未曾宣称他是神。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I just--
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.80,0:29:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Just wish I wouldn't have ever said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.55,0:29:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,只是希望自己从未说过那些话。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Bottom line is this: Jon is still Jon.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.47,0:29:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,归根结底：乔恩依然是乔恩。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}At his core...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.47,0:29:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,在他的本质里……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...he's still a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.43,0:29:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,……他仍是凡人。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, take what I said about supervillains being a direct response...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.56,0:29:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,那么，将我关于超级反派是直接回应……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to the appearance of superheroes...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.69,0:29:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,……超级英雄出现的言论……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and apply that to the current scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.24,0:29:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,……套用到当前局势中。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If you have a being that can destroy...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.45,0:29:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,若存在一个能凭一念之间……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...with a single thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.20,0:29:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,……摧毁一切的存在……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...then the terrifying thing is that there is...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.58,0:29:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,那么可怕之处在于……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...or there soon will be, a counterpoint or an adversary to that being.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.04,0:29:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,……很快就会出现与之抗衡的对立者或敌手。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The universe has a way of finding its own equilibrium, its own level.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.47,0:30:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙自有其寻找平衡与稳定之道。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What worries me is that Dr. Manhattan's nemesis will be arriving soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.77,0:30:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,令我担忧的是，曼哈顿博士的宿敌即将到来。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Of course, some of these masked adventurers...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.48,0:30:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,当然，有些蒙面冒险家……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...never stopped practicing their unique craft.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.23,0:30:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,……从未停止磨练他们独特的技艺。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Eventually time moved forward to a point where their presence was again welcomed...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.32,0:30:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,时光流转至某一刻，他们的存在再次被接纳……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and some would say sorely needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.20,0:30:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,……甚至有人会说已迫在眉睫。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Big city streets festered with violence...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.41,0:30:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,恐吓与犯罪猖獗。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...intimidation and rampant crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.74,0:30:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这正是新型蒙面英雄诞生的绝佳土壤。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A perfect environment for a new breed of masked hero to emerge.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.79,0:30:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,当然，我指的是守望者。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Of course, I speak of the Watchmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.62,0:30:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,如今，随着冷战升级和真正超级存在的介入…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, with the Cold War escalating and the presence of a truly super being...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.92,0:30:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,…成为我们国防的前沿力量…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...at the forefront of our national defense...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.21,0:30:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,…一种日益增长的恐惧与不安似乎正渗透进民众之中。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...a growing fear and restlessness seems to permeate the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.89,0:30:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,只是这一次，恐惧的对象并非罪犯…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Only this time, the fear is not of the criminals...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.72,0:30:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,…而是打击犯罪者本身。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but of the crime fighters themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.93,0:30:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,基恩参议员无疑认为时机已到…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Senator Keene surely thinks that the time has come to put an end...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.56,0:30:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,…该终结蒙面义警的行为了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to masked adventuring.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.10,0:31:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他提出的新法律将有效束缚这些蒙面英雄的羽翼…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}His suggested new laws would effectively clip the wings of these costumed heroes...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.94,0:31:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,…迫使他们摘下自己的面具…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...making them hang up their masks...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.74,0:31:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,…阻止他们在我们美好的街道上行使私刑正义。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and preventing them from practicing vigilante justice in our fair streets.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.12,0:31:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,基恩参议员是个投机主义的…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Senator Keene is an opportunistic...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.33,0:31:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,…空洞符号。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...cipher.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.33,0:31:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,他根本不明白自己在说什么。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He has no idea what he's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.04,0:31:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,真正的问题在于警察部门。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The real problem are the police departments.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.71,0:31:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他们能多借鉴一些这些蒙面英雄的特质…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If they would take a little bit more of what these masked heroes have...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.67,0:31:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,…我们就不需要基恩参议员这样的人了…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...then we wouldn't need people like Senator Keene...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.76,0:31:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,...首先是在参议院。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...in the Senate in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.47,0:31:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我对基恩参议员有何看法？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What do I think about Senator Keene?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.43,0:31:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,听着，我每天都在这里工作。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Listen, l work down here every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.64,0:31:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,每当我遇到麻烦，每当有人在这里痛斥我...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Whenever I'm in trouble, whenever somebody's down here beating me up...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.15,0:31:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,...而我大声呼救时，我不在乎是谁来救我的命。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and l yell for help, l don't care who comes to save my butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.02,0:31:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我不在乎是超级英雄，也不在乎是警察。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't care if it's a superhero. I don't care if it's a cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.65,0:31:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,只要有人在我喊"救命"时出现就行。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}As long as somebody comes when l'm yelling "help."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.24,0:31:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你明白吗？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.49,0:31:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,人们...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}People have...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.99,0:31:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,...需要...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...a need for...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.50,0:31:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,...一位日常英雄。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...an everyday hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.87,0:31:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,无论是否蒙面。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Masked or otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.33,0:32:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,而且，呃...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.30,0:32:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,...那些明辨是非的人...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...people who know right from wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.59,0:32:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,...永远都会是需要的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...will always be in demand.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.73,0:32:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,那么此刻我想稍微谈点个人话题。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So l want to get a little personal here for the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.57,0:32:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你从未结婚。这是为什么？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You never married. Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.83,0:32:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-嗯... -谢谢。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}-Um.... -Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.04,0:32:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我想，如果非要找一个我从未结婚的理由...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, l suppose if there's any one reason why l never got married...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.75,0:32:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,...那是因为...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...it was because...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.46,0:32:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,...嗯，莎莉·朱庇特已经名花有主了。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...well, Sally Jupiter was taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.42,0:32:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't think...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.55,0:32:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,...我对她有好感，这算不上什么大秘密。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...it's any great secret that I had a thing for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.72,0:32:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,当时一半的男性都对她有好感。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Half the male population did.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.06,0:32:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,等我终于鼓起勇气，想约她正式出去约会时...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}By the time l'd rustled up the courage to ask her out on a proper date...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.89,0:33:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...她已经嫁给了她的经纪人。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...she was already married to her manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.52,0:33:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,[轻笑]\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}[CHUCKLES]
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.57,0:33:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,说起来还挺有趣的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's kind of funny when you think of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.24,0:33:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我每天扮成猫头鹰出生入死……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I dress up as an owl and risk my life on a daily basis...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.03,0:33:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,……但到了约女孩出来的时候……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but when it came to asking a girl out...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.08,0:33:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,……我却束手无策。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...it was more than l could manage.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.87,0:33:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,可悲的是，我觉得我们的婚姻从一开始就注定了失败。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sadly, I think our marriage was doomed from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.38,0:33:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我在莎莉生活中的职业身份让我很难成为一个好丈夫。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My professional position in Sally's life made it very difficult to be a good husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.97,0:33:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,作为她的经纪人，我的工作……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It was my job as her manager...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.97,0:33:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,……不仅是接受男人被她吸引的事实……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to not only accept the fact that men were attracted to her...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.47,0:33:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,……还要利用这种吸引力……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but to build on that attraction...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.89,0:33:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,……从中牟利。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to prey upon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.82,0:33:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,霍利斯对你来说非常重要。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hollis was very important to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.61,0:33:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,他是你生命中非常重要的人，对吗？\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He was a very important person in your life, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.86,0:33:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,毫无疑问。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.07,0:33:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,-你们现在还有联系吗？-有的，有的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}-You stay in contact with each other today? -We do. We do.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.28,0:33:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,不过我得说，联系不如我希望的那么频繁。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Not as much as l would like, I must say.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.79,0:34:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道，人生轨迹总会走向不同的方向……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, your life takes you in different directions...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.25,0:34:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,……但那确实是一段不可思议的、梦幻般的时光……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but that was really a magical, magical time...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.83,0:34:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,……我们相聚时总爱聊起那些旧日往事。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and we do like to talk about the old times when we get together.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.96,0:34:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗，我觉得——\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, I think--
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.30,0:34:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得我心里还藏着某种……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think I still have some kind of...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.89,0:34:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,……不成熟的念头……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...half-baked idea that...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.31,0:34:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,……关于夜枭和，呃……\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Nite Owl and, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.14,0:34:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,丝鬼和夜枭总有一天会在一起的。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Silk Spectre are gonna end up together one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.70,0:34:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.78,0:34:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,当初我们采访霍利斯·梅森时...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}When we originally spoke with Hollis Mason...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.33,0:34:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,...他相信他作为夜枭开创的传承...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...he believed that the legacy he'd begun as the Nite Owl...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.54,0:34:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...以及蒙面英雄群体的其他成员...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...along with other members of the masked-hero community...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.13,0:34:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,...将在未来岁月中延续下去。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...would live on for years to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.34,0:34:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他当时不可能知道自己错得多么离谱。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He could not have known how wrong he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.13,0:34:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,本期节目带我们怀旧回顾了这个国家历史上一个多彩的时代...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This has been a nostalgic look back at a colorful time in this nation's past...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.81,0:35:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,...那时我们曾向身着卡通服装的浮夸英雄...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...when we turned to flamboyant heroes with cartoonish outfits...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.02,0:35:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,...寻求道德指引。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...for our moral outlook.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.56,0:35:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,在我们如今生活的后基恩法案时代...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In the post-Keene Act world we now live in...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.15,0:35:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,...蒙面英雄已如同霍利斯·梅森在车库里修理的那些...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the masked heroes are as outdated and irrelevant...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.86,0:35:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,...破旧报废车辆般过时且无关紧要。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...as the old beat-up wrecks that Hollis Mason works on in his garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.90,0:35:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,希望这次对制服冒险者历史的回顾...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We hope that you have found this look back at the history of costumed adventurers...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.07,0:35:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,...能带给各位启迪与新知。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...both enlightening and informative.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.70,0:35:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我是《卡尔佩珀一分钟》的拉里·卡尔佩珀。\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm Larry Culpeper for The Culpeper Minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.92,0:37:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[英文字幕]\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}[ENGLISH SDH]
